      "amount": "1/4 teaspoon"
    },
    {
      "name": "taco shells",
      "amount": "8-10 shells"
    },
    {
      "name": "shredded lettuce",
      "amount": "1 cup"
    },
    {
      "name": "diced tomatoes",
      "amount": "1 cup"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 400 degrees Fahrenheit.",
    "In a large bowl, whisk together grape juice, olive oil, cumin, smoked paprika, black pepper, and salt.",
    "Add the chicken pieces to the bowl and marinate for at least 30 minutes.",
    "Remove the chicken from the marinade and bake in the oven for 20-25 minutes, or until cooked through.",
    "While the chicken is cooking, reduce the marinade over medium heat until thickened and syrupy.",
    "Warm the taco shells according to package instructions.",
    "Assemble the tacos by placing cooked chicken onto a shell, followed by a spoonful of reduced marinade, shredded lettuce, and diced tomatoes.",
    "Serve immediately and enjoy."
  ],
